   <th><a href="msg4504">msg4504 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: vkmc</th>
   <th>Date: 2014-08-01.16:04:54</th>
   <th>
    
   </th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>There is a long list of people wanting to contribute to many projects and there 
is no way for mentors to contact them. This is indeed an important issue.

Some possible approaches to fix this:
- Make the e-mail field for registration a requirement and make sure it is 
always public, at least for the OpenHatch registered users. (Cons: privacy, 
Pros: easy to implement)
- If people mark themselves as "want to help" and they haven't setted the "how 
to contact" field, they should get a warning that there's no way for people to 
contact them. (Cons: people could forget, Pros: keeps privacy and it's fairly 
easy to implement)
- Implement an OpenHatch messaging system. (Cons: hard to implement, Pros: a 
natural and complete solution)

The first two are perhaps the best call for now since implementing a messaging 
system is hard and could take a long time.

Just having a "contact this user" with forwarder, visible at least to mentors, 
would help tremendously.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
